<doc id="40983" wikidata="Q5196478" url="?curid=40983" title="Customer service unit">
<text>In telecommunications, a customer service unit (CSU) is a device that provides an accessing arrangement at a user location to either switched or point-to-point, data-conditioned circuits at a specifically established data signaling rate. 

A CSU provides local loop equalization, transient protection, isolation, and central office loop-back testing capability.

