<doc id="41082" wikidata="Q5347251" url="?curid=41082" title="Effective data transfer rate">
<text>In telecommunications, effective data transfer rate is the average number of units of data, such as bits, characters, blocks, or frames, transferred per unit time from a source and accepted as valid by a sink.

&quot;Note:&quot; The effective data transfer rate is usually expressed in bits, characters, blocks, or frames per second. The effective data transfer rate may be averaged over a period of seconds, minutes, or hours.

