<doc id="41096" wikidata="Q5358086" url="?curid=41096" title="Electromagnetic interference control">
<text>In Electrical systems, such as telecommunications, power electronics, industrial electronics, power engineering; electromagnetic interference &quot;(EMI)&quot; control is the control of radiated and conducted energy such that emissions that are unnecessary for system, subsystem, or equipment operation are reduced, minimized, or eliminated. 

&quot;Note:&quot; Electromagnetic radiated and conducted emissions are controlled regardless of their origin within the system, subsystem, or equipment. Successful EMI control with effective susceptibility control leads to electromagnetic compatibility.

